  "lesson": {
    "id": "0003",
    "title": "Decisions with if",
    "slug": "if-statements",
    "summary": "Make your program branch based on conditions.",
    "sortOrder": 3
  },
  "sections": [
    {
      "id": "0003:s1",
      "heading": "Programs that branch",
      "bodyHtml": "<p>An <code>if</code> statement <strong>skips</strong> some lines depending on a condition.</p><pre><code>if temperature > 25 {\n    fmt.Println(\"It is hot.\")\n} else {\n    fmt.Println(\"It is cool.\")\n}</code></pre>",
      "sortOrder": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "0003:s2",
      "heading": "Comparisons",
      "bodyHtml": "<p>Use <code>==</code> to compare (not <code>=</code>). Common operators: <code>!=</code> <code>&gt;</code> <code>&lt;</code> <code>&gt;=</code> <code>&lt;=</code></p>",
      "sortOrder": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "0003:s3",
      "heading": "Your turn",
      "bodyHtml": "<p>Open <code>practice/decisions/main.go</code>. Add an if/else: print <code>You are an adult.</code> when <code>age &gt;= 18</code>, else <code>You are a minor.</code></p>",
      "sortOrder": 3
    }
  ],
